			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi guys, 
<br />

<br />
249INT mana pool. Avg gear purchased 1-4k a piece a few under 500pp.  With Dogmar. Give you an idea what is soloing here. Nothing special. Never raided even as of yet. No time or pop gear either.
<br />

<br />
Bind by the East Freeport translocator on the dock. Or by the Freeport POK book.
<br />

<br />
At 45th lvl with KEI I went to OOT. Seafurys on this island is great xp but is mana draining until 47th with KEI before you start pulling two to three with one bar. 
<br />

<br />
Find the druid looking ring on the island. You will see a skinny long piece of land where you can set up camp and pull to. Don't want adds. Any add and you gate. End of story don't try it let pet fight and use your only get out of jail card.
<br />

<br />
Water pet focused is what I used. Found focused Air to be weak and went down to fast. Fire pet would do but is still not as effiecient as water IMO on these seafury's.  Armored them with phantom plate and two one handed proc'ing summoned weps. Burnout II. Expeidence. Barrier of Combustion.
<br />

<br />
/pet guard at the top of the mound. Judge your distance and give yourself some back room but allow for running space when mob turns. Don't want an add. You'll notice the seafury's come to about the bottom of the hill before the druid looking spire before they stop. One pops right in front of the spire near where you pull occasionally.
<br />

<br />
Taking em down will require your own tactics with aggro control. I like to Malestrom. Heal pet. Let pet fight a bit. Nuke with 44th lvl Swords of combustion. Heal pet. Wait a bit. Nuke Malestrom again. Wait a bit. Just before the run nuke Combustion again. With Robe of Tempest ( improved damage III ) I can top 708 damage.
<br />

<br />
It's a slow go from 45th to 47th even with KEI cause it requires almost a full mana bar one to two. However at 48th I see I can take 3 before requiring a real mana break. Three cyclops is about a blue bar of exp atm.
<br />

<br />
Need KEI? I'm bound in front of the POK book in Freeport. Gate to POK. Get KEI. Gate back to Freeport and translocate to OOT with an extended 30% KEI that last almost 3hours.
<br />

<br />
GOOD luck gentlemages of squire. Hope this helps new time mages who've not seen OOT yet. 
<br />

<br />
