			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Quaggy poo does not summon, nor does the tainted.  Quag does have a nasty manadrain and a boatload of hitpoints...well at least more than the regular furbies.
<br />

<br />
I spent 45 - 52 here, made decent cash. (before LoY)
<br />

<br />
Now the Corrupted will summon you and beat you down.
<br />

<br />
Instead of just gating when you get an add, make sure you always have a ring of flight in inventory.  Get an add, lev and run to the sisters isle and cast pet as soon as other dies.  The furby has a long run so get him some weps, BO and DS.  You should allready have the furby targeted, so when you see his head bobbing towards you in the water, back up until he comes out, sick pet and then run to ac island.  Rinse and repeat until both are deaderated. exp for both and no lengthy boat rides involved!
<br />

<br />
I spent all those levels in OOT and died once, and it was helping to kill the corrupted.  I always pulled with malo line, and was leved to avoid damage on long pulls.  I used the earth pet and nuked with bolts.
<br />

<br />
Check to see if Gornit camp is open, inbetween furbies you can slap him down, 6 minute spawn, normal hill giant, with hill giant loot, seen up to 53pp on a kill.  Being a gnome mage, I had killer faction with the sisters and with stiens, a 3 hour kei session without Gornit nets about 300-400pp, with Gornit, that jumps to an easy 700-900pp.  
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps...<br />_________________<br />Cislabik Cerebrumide
<br />
65 Arch Convoker (epic'ed)
<br />
Tholuxe Pealls</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
